heading_context: Find overseas customers and export opportunities
chunks.html_content:
Get help selling online overseas and take advantage of special deals negotiated by the government.

And join the e-exporting programme to get:

  • advice on developing a strategy from e-commerce and international trade experts
  • special rates for some of the world’s most popular online selling platforms
  • regular updates on e-commerce trends and opportunities to hear from industry experts and network with other online traders

Contact e-exporting@trade.gov.uk to join the e-exporting programme.

heading_context: Find overseas customers and export opportunities
If you had an OMIS account
chunks.html_content:
The Department for Business and Trade (DBT) has a network of trade specialists who can also help you find overseas customers by:

  • helping you prepare for a trade show or overseas market visit (sometimes grants are available - check with the event organiser)
  • arranging introductions to potential overseas buyers, agents and distributors (there’s a charge for this service)

To find out more, first see the export guidance on great.gov.uk, then contact a trade adviser in your region.

If you had an Overseas Market Introduction Service (OMIS) account and want to talk about something you commissioned, contact a trade adviser in your region or email omis.orders@digital.trade.gov.uk.

heading_context: Find overseas customers and export opportunities
chunks.html_content:
Contact UK Defence and Security Exports (UKDSE) for help exporting products and services related to defence, security, cyber security and civil maritime.

They can help by:

  • providing specialist export advice and intelligence
  • supporting and promoting UK industry at domestic and overseas events, including major defence and security exhibitions
  • coordinating cross-government activity to support specific export and investment campaigns
  • building relationships with industry and overseas governments to raise awareness of UK industry
